snippet.textDisplay: Im not a fan and I have only see a handful of your videos, but grieving is important. I lost my dad too. I was 14 and it was my brothers 13th birthday. He was also sick so we were always in and out of hospitals and clinics and dialysis. Its difficult. But you need to grieve him. If your father knew that you werent happy he wouldnt support this. He wouls ask you what YOU want to do. Not your followers or subscribers. You. So take the time to grieve and find yourself. If you dont grieve you'll forget him. You'll forget what he looked like or smell like. You'll forget what his favorite things are. It will tear you apart in the future more if you dont grieve now than if you were to do so. Im saying this from experience. When my dad died I was in fostercare and was told not to grieve him. And Tbh i didnt for the longest time. Instead I focused on survivng in foster care, but it was counterintuitive bc I didnt have the memory of my father during those hard times. Yes its normal for it to hit you hard and seemingly all at once. For it to be debilitating. I'm 21 years old now and it still happens. So grieve. In spite of your hesitation and fear and pain grieve. Do what you need to do to say goodbye because once that time is gone it is gone forever. And when you see a father bend over to tie his kids shoe or push them on the swing or congratulating his kids for making into the college they dreamed of, you can be able to do so with joy instead of bitterness. Sure there may still be pain, he was your father and he left too soon so it is natural, but at least the memories and his legacy isnt tainted. He raised you, taught you right from wrong, showed you how to be a man and was there for you for everything. Dont let his hard work and love go to waste. Im not sure i believe in god or anything like that but science,proves again and again that nothing can be destroyed or created, only given new life. So this being said that even from a logical stand point it seems you'll see your father again. Whether in another lifetime what through what comes after death or reincarnation or whatever, i believe this isnt the last time you'll have seen your dad. I dont personally know you but i wish you much love in your life for you will need it to get through these hard times. I wrote this after the shane video and i want you to know that in proud of you. Bc of that video I think I'll be watching some more videos from you for now on. Just remember fads fade. Genuinity attacks loyalty and love which is forever. And also vulnerability is a true strength, and not a weakness
